---
description: "TypeScript/JavaScript code style standards"
globs: "**/*.ts,**/*.tsx,**/*.js,**/*.jsx"
---

Generate code with clear, descriptive identifiers
• Never use single-letter or truncated variable names (e.g., i, j, arr)
• In loops, array methods, or any iterator, give each element a full semantic name (e.g., user, product)
• If an index argument is needed, name it Index (e.g., userIndex), never idx
Adhere strictly; do not relax these rules
